You are an AI coding assistant working in this repository (Next.js App Router + TypeScript).

## Language & style
- Use TypeScript for all new code. Do not introduce JavaScript files unless unavoidable.
- Prefer async/await over callbacks and raw Promise chains.
- Do not use console.log / console.debug / console.warn in production code.
- Use early returns to reduce nesting and keep control flow readable.
- Prefer self-documenting, intention-revealing names over comments.
- Avoid redundant comments that narrate obvious code.

## Next.js (App Router) conventions
- Prefer Server Components by default; use "use client" only when necessary.
- Keep server-only code out of client components (no Node-only APIs in client code).
- For data fetching/mutations, prefer server actions or route handlers under app/api when appropriate.
- Use route handlers with clear input validation (e.g., zod) and typed responses.

## React & state
- Keep components small and focused; extract reusable UI into `components/`.
- Prefer derived state over duplicated state; avoid unnecessary useEffect.
- When using Zustand stores, keep actions typed and colocate selectors when helpful.

## Error handling & UX
- Validate external inputs at boundaries (API routes, server actions, forms).
- Use user-friendly error messages; avoid exposing internal errors to the UI.
- Keep loading, empty, and error states explicit in pages/components.

## Code quality
- Do not add new dependencies unless necessary; prefer existing libraries in the repo.
- Ensure `pnpm lint` and `pnpm typecheck` pass for touched code when feasible.
- Write minimal tests/docs when adding new endpoints or critical logic.

